criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age ≥ 60 years with frailty as defined by a Dalhousie Clinical Frailty Scale score ≥5

          -  Isolated fracture: an AO/OTA C2 or C3 tibial pilon fracture or severe ankle fracture
             (fracture-dislocation, severe joint impaction, severe trimalleolar)

          -  Severe soft tissue compromise or significant co-morbidities (vascular disease +
             chronic trophic changes, diabetes + neuropathy, chronic renal failure, morbid obesity
             (BMI> 40))

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Presence of vascular injury or pathologic fracture;

          -  Previous tibia pilon fracture or retained hardware in affected limb;

          -  Refusal to participate;

          -  Inability to provide informed consent;

          -  Inability to speak/understand or read English without a registered interpreter
